title: For Sale:  FN Browning Hi-Power 9mm FS
postcontent:
I’m selling a surplus original, numbers matching FN Browning Hi-Power. According to the serial numbers it was manufactured in 1987 at the FN Herstal plant. The bore is in excellent condition. I tested it out at the range shortly after buying it and it feeds standard ball & hollow point ammo like a champ. I ran about 150 rounds that was a mix of brass, nickel plated, and steel cased ammo through it with no problems. The gun comes with a 13 round factory mag but Mecgar makes 15 rounders which folks have had good luck with if you’re looking for a more modern magazine capacity. The finish is an epoxy coating which is worn but the metal underneath it is in great shape. This was a trade-in from Austrian security forces and like most such guns looks to have been holstered a lot and fired very little. I have left the gun completely stock, as it left the FN plant, so the springs are all as-issued and the magazine disconnect is still intact. 

If you're looking to own a piece of history without breaking the bank this is a great opportunity! Most Browning Hi-Powers cost double the asking price and this one has a neat history as an actual fielded service pistol. 

SOLD

Please let me know if you have any questions. Best way to get ahold of me is via email: REDACTED
